30
00:01:23.220 --> 00:01:24.150
All right.

31
00:01:24.150 --> 00:01:28.483
So we just saw the SURMOUNT trials come out on tirzepatide,

32
00:01:29.730 --> 00:01:32.290
and what they did was they continued

33
00:01:33.840 --> 00:01:35.730
after they got to their goal weight,

34
00:01:35.730 --> 00:01:37.680
they stopped some of the patients

35
00:01:37.680 --> 00:01:40.380
and continued some on the same dose they were on,

36
00:01:40.380 --> 00:01:43.620
and the patients who stopped started gaining weight again.

37
00:01:43.620 --> 00:01:47.220
And the patients that they continued on had this continued

38
00:01:47.220 --> 00:01:50.850
slow kind of trending of weight loss.

39
00:01:50.850 --> 00:01:54.360
No one has looked at what we're going to do with these.

40
00:01:54.360 --> 00:01:56.850
Are we gonna, should we put them on a low dose

41
00:01:56.850 --> 00:01:58.113
of these medicines?

42
00:01:59.340 --> 00:02:02.040
Should we use the medicine once a month?

43
00:02:02.040 --> 00:02:04.350
We have no data on any of that.

44
00:02:04.350 --> 00:02:06.360
But the answer, the short answer is yes,

45
00:02:06.360 --> 00:02:08.490
we're gonna see rebound weight gain.

46
00:02:08.490 --> 00:02:10.890
Hopefully, some of these patients have, you know,

47
00:02:10.890 --> 00:02:13.560
the weight loss has taken a, you know, a couple of years

48
00:02:13.560 --> 00:02:15.990
to get to where they, we stopped the medicine,

49
00:02:15.990 --> 00:02:18.120
and hopefully, some of those people have made enough

50
00:02:18.120 --> 00:02:21.660
lifestyle change that they'll do a better job

51
00:02:21.660 --> 00:02:22.680
of keeping the weight off.

52
00:02:22.680 --> 00:02:24.773
<v ->Which is the issue with the payment right now,</v>

53
00:02:24.773 --> 00:02:26.400
because when you'd come off,

54
00:02:26.400 --> 00:02:27.450
then you gain the weight back.

55
00:02:27.450 --> 00:02:30.810
And we don't have, Belinda says,

56
00:02:30.810 --> 00:02:32.580
we don't know what the data looks like.

