00:02:34.470 --> 00:02:35.820
and what that's gonna look like?

59
00:02:35.820 --> 00:02:36.870
Okay, that's the problem

60
00:02:36.870 --> 00:02:39.663
in terms of 3rd party payment right now so.

61
00:02:41.160 --> 00:02:44.663
<v ->Do, oh, you-</v>
<v ->No, go ahead, Dr. Vail.</v>

62
00:02:44.663 --> 00:02:48.600
<v ->So will limited weight gain also prevent obesity</v>

63
00:02:48.600 --> 00:02:50.220
in children whose mothers are overweight

64
00:02:50.220 --> 00:02:52.410
or obese going into pregnancy?

65
00:02:52.410 --> 00:02:54.900
So the answer is actually yes.

66
00:02:54.900 --> 00:02:57.570
It gives them a better starting point

67
00:02:57.570 --> 00:03:00.720
than if you just let mothers gain weight at, you know,

68
00:03:00.720 --> 00:03:02.883
crazy rates during their pregnancy,

69
00:03:03.810 --> 00:03:06.090
but once they're born, then you've got,

70
00:03:06.090 --> 00:03:08.820
then now you have a whole new set of things.

71
00:03:08.820 --> 00:03:10.650
But, you know, do you ever wonder

72
00:03:10.650 --> 00:03:13.710
how you see all these heavy women walking around

73
00:03:13.710 --> 00:03:15.630
with their little skinny kids?

74
00:03:15.630 --> 00:03:19.200
And the thing is, is that when kids are little,

75
00:03:19.200 --> 00:03:21.390
if you don't, if you just offer them food,

76
00:03:21.390 --> 00:03:22.260
they will eat what,

77
00:03:22.260 --> 00:03:23.940
they'll eat when they're hungry

78
00:03:23.940 --> 00:03:25.350
and, you know, they don't have a lot

79
00:03:25.350 --> 00:03:26.460
of other issues going on.

80
00:03:26.460 --> 00:03:27.660
So they just eat when they're hungry

81
00:03:27.660 --> 00:03:30.360
and they have, you know, they wanna go play

82
00:03:30.360 --> 00:03:34.380
and you know, if you let them do that, they'll self-regulate

83
00:03:34.380 --> 00:03:36.030
and they'll be a healthy weight.

84
00:03:36.030 --> 00:03:38.370
But then we start, you know, feeding them

85
00:03:38.370 --> 00:03:42.450
the wrong kind of foods and doing things to them that,

86
00:03:43.890 --> 00:03:45.690
you know, changing their behaviors

87
00:03:45.690 --> 00:03:48.210
so that they eat unhealthy like we do.

88
00:03:48.210 --> 00:03:52.620
And so it's a beautiful microcosm

89
00:03:52.620 --> 00:03:55.500
to look at little kids,

90
00:03:55.500 --> 00:03:58.410
unless we're doing something to them,

91
00:03:58.410 --> 00:04:00.723
will maintain a healthy weight.

92
00:04:02.240 --> 00:04:05.490
And so, but then the habits that we put on them

93
00:04:05.490 --> 00:04:10.490
as they get older will often lead to weight gain.

94
00:04:10.530 --> 00:04:14.520
So you have to look at the whole loop.

95
00:04:14.520 --> 00:04:16.920
And then someone asked me about, you know,

96
00:04:16.920 --> 00:04:18.360
about these behavioral, you know,

97
00:04:18.360 --> 00:04:22.620
how do you find these behavioral weight loss programs and,

