123
00:05:35.010 --> 00:05:38.400
What's the safest and most efficacious muscle relaxant

124
00:05:38.400 --> 00:05:40.774
to use for acute low back pain?

125
00:05:40.774 --> 00:05:43.380
(Dr. Weismiller and Dr. Garry laughing)

126
00:05:43.380 --> 00:05:46.110
None, I mean, they all have their,

127
00:05:46.110 --> 00:05:47.700
they all have their side effects.

128
00:05:47.700 --> 00:05:51.390
I mean, so there isn't really one

129
00:05:51.390 --> 00:05:56.390
that is safer than others or more effective than others.

130
00:05:56.700 --> 00:05:59.580
It depends, you just have to read your patient.

131
00:05:59.580 --> 00:06:02.580
I mean, if they're really anxious

132
00:06:02.580 --> 00:06:05.910
and they need some more maybe sedative properties,

133
00:06:05.910 --> 00:06:10.910
then maybe I'll use cyclobenzaprine or tizanidine.

134
00:06:11.040 --> 00:06:14.913
If they don't seem like they need that,

135
00:06:16.890 --> 00:06:18.720
I may choose something different,

136
00:06:18.720 --> 00:06:22.350
but there's really no good answer to that question

137
00:06:22.350 --> 00:06:25.710
because as a class, they all have problems,

138
00:06:25.710 --> 00:06:27.417
especially as I get into older patients.

139
00:06:27.417 --> 00:06:29.943
<v ->And is there one you don't recommend?</v>

140
00:06:32.010 --> 00:06:33.090
<v ->No, not necessarily.</v>

141
00:06:33.090 --> 00:06:37.360
What I would tell you is never prescribe

142
00:06:37.360 --> 00:06:39.960
cyclobenzaprine in a 10 milligram dose,

143
00:06:39.960 --> 00:06:43.560
prescribe it in five and let the patient titrate

144
00:06:43.560 --> 00:06:45.630
because, you know,

145
00:06:45.630 --> 00:06:48.180
you're gonna give them 10 milligram pills,

146
00:06:48.180 --> 00:06:50.040
they're gonna get dizzy or tired,

147
00:06:50.040 --> 00:06:53.250
or you have some urinary retention

148
00:06:53.250 --> 00:06:54.600
and they'll never take it again.

149
00:06:54.600 --> 00:06:57.100
And they might have gotten good relief from it so.

150
00:06:59.640 --> 00:07:04.640
Can venlafaxine be used in chronic back pain

151
00:07:05.130 --> 00:07:08.430
in place of duloxetine as an SNRI?

152
00:07:08.430 --> 00:07:09.690
Great question.

153
00:07:09.690 --> 00:07:14.520
I can tell you that the evidence that at 37 1/2 milligrams

154
00:07:14.520 --> 00:07:17.280
or 75 milligrams, the answer is no,

155
00:07:17.280 --> 00:07:19.920
but beyond that, it hasn't been studied.

156
00:07:19.920 --> 00:07:23.430
So the question is, is this a drug effect

157
00:07:23.430 --> 00:07:24.900
or is it a class effect?

158
00:07:24.900 --> 00:07:26.250
And so we run into these,

159
00:07:26.250 --> 00:07:28.530
