00:11:07.320 --> 00:11:11.040
do we need two fasting glucose values to diagnose diabetes?

244
00:11:11.040 --> 00:11:12.480
You need two values.

245
00:11:12.480 --> 00:11:14.403
You can do a fasting and A1C.

246
00:11:15.660 --> 00:11:18.480
Yes, I realize there are patients that come in

247
00:11:18.480 --> 00:11:21.300
and you know, their sugar is 400

248
00:11:21.300 --> 00:11:24.360
and do you really need another value?

249
00:11:24.360 --> 00:11:26.220
No, but you're going to get another value

250
00:11:26.220 --> 00:11:28.560
