00:24:27.060 --> 00:24:30.663
if somebody had a completely normal DXA at the age of 65?

541
00:24:32.220 --> 00:24:34.980
There are no good guidelines for that, okay?

542
00:24:34.980 --> 00:24:37.050
So a lot of my patients are new to me

543
00:24:37.050 --> 00:24:38.790
at the age of, they move in,

544
00:24:38.790 --> 00:24:40.740
and I see them for the first time when they're 85.

545
00:24:40.740 --> 00:24:42.450
And I say, "When's your last DXA scan?"

546
00:24:42.450 --> 00:24:44.340
