688
00:31:33.990 --> 00:31:37.050
A couple questions about different types of stones

689
00:31:37.050 --> 00:31:40.230
like HCTZ, uric acid stones,

690
00:31:40.230 --> 00:31:41.880
is there a correlation between the two?

691
00:31:41.880 --> 00:31:44.340
So this is a good question because if you have a stone,

692
00:31:44.340 --> 00:31:47.880
the reason why you want to identify what type of stone it is

693
00:31:47.880 --> 00:31:50.640
is because each of the five different types of stones

694
00:31:50.640 --> 00:31:54.990
that can be formed all come from a very specific process.

695
00:31:54.990 --> 00:31:56.640
If you have a calcium phosphate stone,

696
00:31:56.640 --> 00:32:00.450
remember we talked about increased pH forms

697
00:32:00.450 --> 00:32:01.620
calcium phosphate stones.

698
00:32:01.620 --> 00:32:05.070
If you have increased oxalate,

699
00:32:05.070 --> 00:32:06.810
which comes from sweet tea.

700
00:32:06.810 --> 00:32:08.730
Sweet tea has a lot of oxalate,

701
00:32:08.730 --> 00:32:10.893
so does rhubarb pie and stuff like that,

702
00:32:12.240 --> 00:32:14.340
that's my home place,

703
00:32:14.340 --> 00:32:17.400
that puts you at greater risk of a calcium oxalate stone.

704
00:32:17.400 --> 00:32:20.163
If you have gout, you have a greater risk of a, you know,

705
00:32:20.163 --> 00:32:21.630
of a uric acid stone.

706
00:32:21.630 --> 00:32:23.100
If you have an infection,

707
00:32:23.100 --> 00:32:26.370
you have a greater risk of a struvite stone, et cetera.

708
00:32:26.370 --> 00:32:28.110
If you're a hyper cystine producer,

709
00:32:28.110 --> 00:32:29.880
you have a greater risk of cystine stone.

710
00:32:29.880 --> 00:32:31.200
So that's why it is important

711
00:32:31.200 --> 00:32:36.033
to actually identify the type of stone that you have.

712
00:32:37.350 --> 00:32:40.113
I'm gonna turn it over to you, I'm gonna look at that.

713
00:32:41.250 --> 00:32:42.083
<v Dr. Weismiller>Dr. Blackwelder,</v>

