00:32:45.810 --> 00:32:48.370
<v ->Yep, so somebody asked about</v>

717
00:32:49.800 --> 00:32:53.550
prolonged QT with Zofran looking at risks.

718
00:32:53.550 --> 00:32:54.630
And this is worth mentioning

719
00:32:54.630 --> 00:32:56.040
'cause I see this from our residents a lot

720
00:32:56.040 --> 00:32:59.193
and there's so many medicines that have a prolonged QT risk,

721
00:33:01.110 --> 00:33:04.080
you know, according to our pharmacist and talking to him,

722
00:33:04.080 --> 00:33:05.730
the studies with prolonged QT with,

723
00:33:05.730 --> 00:33:07.920
on ondansetron were like 32 milligrams

724
00:33:07.920 --> 00:33:10.980
of people getting that dose, you know,

725
00:33:10.980 --> 00:33:12.960
and my response to that is, you know,

726
00:33:12.960 --> 00:33:14.940
that's why we have EKGs.

727
00:33:14.940 --> 00:33:15.923
So if you're concerned about it,

728
00:33:15.923 --> 00:33:17.640
get the EKG and make sure

729
00:33:17.640 --> 00:33:20.010
and then choose the safer option.

730
00:33:20.010 --> 00:33:21.900
It also goes back to the additive effect

731
00:33:21.900 --> 00:33:25.020
of being on multiple medicines that prolong QT.

732
00:33:25.020 --> 00:33:26.250
So maybe you really look at it

733
00:33:26.250 --> 00:33:28.950
and you start whittling away on what people are on

734
00:33:28.950 --> 00:33:30.393
to decrease that risk.

735
00:33:32.130 --> 00:33:32.963
<v Dr. Weismiller>Dr. Gilmer,</v>

736
00:33:32.963 --> 00:33:35.040
remember Odansetron is FDA approved

737
00:33:35.040 --> 00:33:37.953
for one indication, nausea associated with chemotherapy.

