1398
01:01:36.090 --> 01:01:37.277
<v ->So what's the difference between</v>

1399
01:01:37.277 --> 01:01:40.350
erythrasma and intertrigo?

1400
01:01:40.350 --> 01:01:45.330
They both look very similar and are in the similar areas.

1401
01:01:45.330 --> 01:01:48.150
Intertrigo may be a little moisture looking,

1402
01:01:48.150 --> 01:01:50.190
a little bit more itchy,

1403
01:01:50.190 --> 01:01:52.980
but the key is to do the Wood's lamp exam.

1404
01:01:52.980 --> 01:01:53.820
At the Wood's lamp,

1405
01:01:53.820 --> 01:01:57.480
looks like it's a coral pink, red fluorescence,

1406
01:01:57.480 --> 01:02:00.620
that's erythrasma rather than intertrigo.

1407
01:02:02.071 --> 01:02:03.330
A question about the difference

1408
01:02:03.330 --> 01:02:07.170
between lichen simplex chronicus and neural dermatitis,

1409
01:02:07.170 --> 01:02:08.790
they're actually very similar

1410
01:02:08.790 --> 01:02:11.740
and some people would consider them the same thing

1411
01:02:11.740 --> 01:02:14.430
and a chronic itchy rash that you scratch

1412
01:02:14.430 --> 01:02:16.770
and scratching makes it worse

1413
01:02:16.770 --> 01:02:20.587
and may either be in plaques or excoriations,

1414
01:02:22.121 --> 01:02:24.210
but they're very similar.

1415
01:02:24.210 --> 01:02:29.210
Question about shingles vaccine and how long will it last?

1416
01:02:29.760 --> 01:02:34.140
Shingrix, according to CDC, has about a 90% effectiveness

1417
01:02:34.140 --> 01:02:36.333
for about seven years.

1418
01:02:37.740 --> 01:02:39.360
Question about telling difference between

1419
01:02:39.360 --> 01:02:41.460
hot tub folliculitis

1420
01:02:41.460 --> 01:02:44.700
and hot tub pseudomonas folliculitis.

1421
01:02:44.700 --> 01:02:47.070
Whether I know how to do that is do a punch biopsy

1422
01:02:47.070 --> 01:02:48.670
the folliculitis and culture it.

1423
01:02:49.590 --> 01:02:51.120
But the assumption is that

1424
01:02:51.120 --> 01:02:53.850
the folliculitis is probably a gram negative.

1425
01:02:53.850 --> 01:02:56.100
Pseudomonas is in that group.

1426
01:02:56.100 --> 01:02:58.680
If you treat them with ciprofloxacin.

1427
01:02:58.680 --> 01:03:01.350
If they don't resolve initially,

1428
01:03:01.350 --> 01:03:04.203
the pseudomonas should be covered by the ciprofloxacin.

1429
01:03:07.500 --> 01:03:11.010
How long can scabies survive out of a host?

1430
01:03:11.010 --> 01:03:13.560
