1451
01:03:54.030 --> 01:03:56.010
How do you screen for amblyopia?

1452
01:03:56.010 --> 01:03:57.660
That is, so for younger children,

1453
01:03:57.660 --> 01:03:58.860
you do the cover on cover test.

1454
01:03:58.860 --> 01:04:00.690
So you cover one eye and then you switch it

1455
01:04:00.690 --> 01:04:03.360
and you wanna make sure that both eyes should stay straight.

1456
01:04:03.360 --> 01:04:05.940
If one eye drifts away when you cover it,

1457
01:04:05.940 --> 01:04:08.760
that is someone you need to refer.

1458
01:04:08.760 --> 01:04:10.200
Why should walkers be avoided?

1459
01:04:10.200 --> 01:04:13.800
